<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="283" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1375]" pageId="3" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1313,1339]" pageId="3" pageNumber="283">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin word “ 
<emphasis box="[921,1042,1313,1338]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="283">asymmeter</emphasis>
”, meaning asymmetrical, referring to the saccus with two arms unequal in length.
</paragraph>
